<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5661] The heuristic to derive the password type from the metatype id does not work reliably</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5661</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3168&quot; title=&quot;Add support for new PASSWORD attribute type of Metatype service&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-3168&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-3168&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; support for password meta type data has been added. Not only meta data with type=&quot;password&quot; are detected as such but also string meta data containing &quot;password&quot; in the id (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/felix/blame/trunk/webconsole/src/main/java/org/apache/felix/webconsole/internal/configuration/MetaTypeSupport.java#L183&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/felix/blame/trunk/webconsole/src/main/java/org/apache/felix/webconsole/internal/configuration/MetaTypeSupport.java#L183&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;br/&gt;
This heuristic does not really work well. E.g. in Oak there is property with id=&quot;passwordHashAlgorithm&quot; (type string) (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/2acda3156cfad9993310e7aa0492cdc0b65aa5f7/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/security/authentication/token/TokenConfigurationImpl.java#L65&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/jackrabbit-oak/blob/2acda3156cfad9993310e7aa0492cdc0b65aa5f7/oak-core/src/main/java/org/apache/jackrabbit/oak/security/authentication/token/TokenConfigurationImpl.java#L65&lt;/a&gt;) which should clearly not be detected as password type.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
